      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHALED IT (2) scored by 3.5 lengths last time (19.15) in a Grade 4 over 340m at this track. Rates on top and should go close. ZIPPING POITIER (6) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only half a length (30.24) behind Reiko Jetson at Launceston. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Can feature again. SHERWOOD BOYS (3) ran below best last time finishing fifth (16.47) over 278m at Launceston in a Grade 5. Has a good record here at this journey. Expected to run well. DEADLY GRIN (4) is building a nice sequence of wins – must be respected.",
